The subject teaches wheelchair skills and their assessment, but also different transfers that are related with wheelchair using. The course also introduces how to choose the right wheelchair and what is correct sitting position.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the subject is to provide basic knowledge and practical skills for assessing, performing and also teaching the main
wheelchair skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course, the student: -	can move safely and correctly with a wheelchair on flat and uneven surfaces, get over simpler obstacles; -	can stay, move and get over obstacles in the "wheelie" position, can ascend and descend curbs; -	can assess wheelchair skills; -	understands how wheelchair set up affects the moving characteristics and how to choose the right wheelchair for the patient; -	can safely and ergonomically guide and assist the patient during different transfers associated with wheelchair (for example from the wheelchair to the car, to the toilet, to the floor and back to the wheelchair; -	is able to safely and ergonomically guide and assist the patient when ascending or descending stairs.
